sweet
------------------------------------------------------------
rice desert
| egg in jiu niang, high heat
| shake egg around to seperate yolk and white
| shake white into jiu niang, but do not break yolk
| done when yolk is able to be picked up (want yolk runny)
| add mirin as needed
+
| coat pan with neutral oil
| sugar
| chop mochi into sections that will melt into a sheet
| low heat, flipping frequently to heat evenly
| done when fried light brown/crunchy
=>
| spoon jiu niang into small bowl/cup
| yolk on top
| cut fried mochi into strips
| place mochi strips
